      "content": "## RESEARCH COMPLETE\n\n**Phase:** 21.1 - Execute-Slash-Command SDK Redesign\n**Confidence:** HIGH\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **SDK `session.command()` exists in v1 (installed) at `dist/gen/sdk.gen.d.ts:186`** with body: `{ command, arguments, agent?, model?, messageID? }` — covers all 7 SPEC requirements. No `parts` field in v1; subtask routing must use `session.prompt()`.\n\n2. **`client.command.list()` provides preflight** — returns `Array<Command>` with `{ name, description, agent?, model?, template, subtask? }` — native command existence checking.\n\n3. **ToolContext has NO client** — the `client` is injected via factory closure (`createExecuteSlashCommandTool(client)` called from `plugin.ts:408`), not available from `ctx`.\n\n4. **SDK v1 vs v2 gap matters** — `PluginInput.client` is v1 SDK. v1 `session.command()` has simpler body (no `parts`, no `variant`). Don't use v2 types.\n\n5. **Subtask routing via `session.prompt()` with `SubtaskPartInput`** — not via `session.command()` which doesn't support subtask parts.\n\n6. **Agent switching is server-side** — `session.command({ agent })` triggers `SessionNextAgentSwitched` event. Mechanism (b) (restore) would need a follow-up call.\n\n7. **CommandBundle type at `types.ts:4-17` is missing `model` and `subtask`** — either extend it or use SDK `Command` type for frontmatter reading.\n\n### File Created\n`.planning/phases/21.1-execute-slash-command-sdk-redesign-agent-switching-native-sd/21.1-RESEARCH.md`\n\n### Confidence Assessment\n| Area | Level | Reason |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| Standard Stack | HIGH | All SDK types verified from installed `node_modules` — exact signatures confirmed |\n| Architecture | HIGH | Patterns derived directly from SDK type definitions and existing project structure |\n| Pitfalls | HIGH | Based on reading current code + SDK type mismatches between v1/v2, session queue behavior, and CommandBundle type gaps |\n\n### Open Questions\n1. Whether `session.command()` queue